				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The MCU on your Arduino board will be acting as the 2A03's ROM and RAM. So you'll need to spoon-feed opcodes onto the eight data bus pins and react to what it outputs on M2 and a subset of the address lines. Most of these signals change at 1.8 MHz, one-twelfth of the input clock.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

