			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Make atmega control CLK to the pin 29. This CLK pin should be connected to one of atmega's timer outputs.<br />During idle time (for example, when USB communication is in progress), you want to keep CLK at stable frequency to make generation of stable fruequency square/triangle sound waves. At that time, you also fed $4C to data bus to mimic JMP $4C4C opcode.<br /><br />When executing special commands (like: play sound at frequency f), you programatically control CLK (and R/!W, address and data bus) to mimic feding asm opcodes.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
